The paper deals with wireless power transfer and backscatter communication in a network architecture for the Internet of Things. It uses stochastic geometry to derive tractable expressions for the coverage probability and capacity of the network. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
